    interest_bucket: 'tech',
    title: 'Tech Cities Around the World',
    body: `Every tech city has its own special character. Some tech hubs are old and well-established. Some are new and growing fast. Big tech cities have modern buildings and fast internet connections everywhere. Riyadh is becoming a major technology capital in the Middle East. It has new tech parks and innovation centres with impressive buildings. Omar wants to build the next big Saudi tech company in Riyadh. Tariq visits different tech cities around the world for inspiration. He travels to San Francisco, Singapore, and Dubai. Each city does tech differently. San Francisco has big old companies and new startups in different neighborhoods. Singapore has a strong government support system. Dubai has a very new and ambitious tech scene. Transportation between tech hubs is easy with fast airports and good connections. Nada worked in London before coming back to Riyadh. She loves that Riyadh is growing so fast. The government is investing in new tech neighborhoods and smart city infrastructure. New tech companies are building their headquarters in Riyadh's streets. Old neighborhoods are being transformed into creative tech hubs. Every tech city needs good internet, smart talent, and supportive rules to grow. Ruba says the best tech cities in the world all have one thing in common: they attract people who want to build the future. Riyadh is becoming one of those cities.`,
