    interest_bucket: 'tech',
    title: 'The Green Tech Office',
    body: `Many people think tech offices are just screens and keyboards. But the best startup offices in Saudi Arabia have beautiful green spaces that inspire creativity. These green areas help engineers and designers think better and feel happier. The startup office near King Fahd Road has a beautiful rooftop garden. It has many trees and green plants around every corner. It is a comfortable and inspiring place for the team. Omar codes from the garden some mornings. The trees and fresh air help him think more clearly. Nada loves the garden most of all. She sketches new design ideas while sitting under the trees. The office also has a small fish pond near the main entrance. It feels peaceful and calm. The lights in the outdoor area are smart LEDs that adjust to the time of day. They make the space beautiful in the evenings when the team works late. The office has a small sandy relaxation zone that feels like a beach corner. Team members use it for informal meetings and brainstorming. Tariq believes green spaces are essential in tech offices. He says that nature helps the human brain stay creative and avoid burnout. Ruba tracks team mood scores and notices that scores are always higher on days when people spend time in the garden. Green tech offices are better places to work. They attract and retain the best talent.`,
