    interest_bucket: 'tech',
    title: 'Tech Cycles: Four Seasons of a Startup',
    body: `A startup goes through different phases every year, just like the four seasons. These cycles bring different types of challenges and opportunities to the tech team. The launch season is the hottest period. The temperature of excitement is at its highest. The sun of public attention is very strong. The team works the longest hours. Omar and Nada sleep very little during a product launch. The growth season feels like spring. The weather of the product improves. More users discover the app. New features make the product cooler and more beautiful. The team feels energised and optimistic. The optimisation season is like autumn. The temperature cools down. The team reviews what is working and what is not. Ruba analyses user data carefully. Tariq makes hard decisions about the product direction. The planning season is the coldest period. The team steps back and thinks about the next year. They write new plans and set new goals. Sometimes snow in the form of unexpected problems falls during this season. But the team stays warm with hot coffee and a clear vision. Omar says each season makes the startup stronger. Understanding the cycles helps the team prepare and perform better. Smart startup founders know which season they are in at all times. Every season has its own weather and its own challenges. Knowing this makes you a better builder.`,
