    title: 'How a Tech App Works Every Day',
    body: `A tech app is like an amazing machine that never stops working. Every day, it does thousands of tasks to keep users healthy, happy, and connected. Omar thinks of the app as a living system with many parts that must work together. The server is the heart of the app. It pumps data to every part of the system. If the server has a problem, the whole app feels sick. The database is the stomach. It stores and processes all user information. When the database is slow, users wait and get frustrated. The user interface is the face. It is what users see and touch. Nada works on the face every day to make it beautiful and easy to use. The API is the hand of the app. It reaches out and connects the app to other systems and services. It handles every request and sends the right response back. The analytics module is the eye. It watches how users behave and reports what it sees. This helps the team understand what is working and what is not. Ruba looks at the analytics every morning to check the health of the product. The backend code is the head. It controls the logic of everything. Every decision passes through it. When the head has a bug, the whole app behaves in unexpected ways. Omar fixes the head bugs carefully. A tech app is healthy when every part works together smoothly. Good engineers keep all parts strong and fast.`,
